modules.description: Provides functions to send HTTP requests with customizable timeout, headers, and port, and handles request formatting for a specific API. Works with string-based URLs, host names, and a custom request type encapsulating query parameters. Used to interact with music recommendation services by submitting user listening data.

Provides functions to send HTTP requests with customizable timeout, headers, and port, and returns the response as a string. Works with the `request` type to structure outgoing HTTP messages and uses a float reference for the default timeout value. Used to fetch data from remote servers with precise control over connection parameters.

Provides functions to fetch artist information, track scrobbles, and search for music data from Lastfm. Works with JSON-encoded responses and opaque session tokens. Used to integrate music metadata and user activity into OCaml applications.
Provides the API version string for Last.fm interactions. Works with string data to ensure compatibility with the Last.fm API. Used to construct requests that require a specific API version.

Handles HTTP requests to the Last.fm API with customizable timeout, headers, and port settings. Operates on string-based URLs and request structures to fetch data from specified hosts. Used to retrieve specific API responses like user profiles or track information.
